#: ../new/cloak/sensorarray.rst:6
msgid "Sensor Arrays"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/cloak/sensorarray.rst:8
msgid ""
"Sensor Arrays are buildings that can detect enemy stealth units and "
"structures, as well as subterranean unit movements. The feature was "
"introduced along with Cloak Generators in :game:`Tiberian Sun`, but "
"didn't work correctly in :game:`Red Alert 2`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/cloak/sensorarray.rst:17
msgid "Changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/cloak/sensorarray.rst:19
msgid ""
":tag:`SensorArray=yes` uses :tag:`SensorsSight=` as range to detect "
"stealth and subterranean units, while :game:`Tiberian Sun` reused the "
"Cloak Generator range. This is also used to draw the radial indicator."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/cloak/sensorarray.rst:23
msgid ""
"The bug that the sensor stayed active even after the Sensor Array was "
"destroyed is fixed."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/cloak/sensorarray.rst:26
msgid ""
"Sensor Arrays were not supposed to be powered or to change owner (by "
"capture or mind-control) and weren't updated for temporal weapons. All of"
" this should work now."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/cloak/sensorarray.rst:30
msgid ""
"Two new EVA warnings have been added, :value:`EVA_CloakedUnitDetected` "
"and :value:`EVA_SubterraneanUnitDetected`, which are played when a "
"detector like a Sensor Array detects cloaked units or units moving "
"underground respectively."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/cloak/sensorarray.rst:34
msgid ""
"You have to add these EVA voices to :file:`evamd.ini` before you can use "
"them. The game does not contain audio files for the three original EVA "
"voices."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/cloak/sensorarray.rst:44
msgid "Suppress Sensor Array Warnings"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/cloak/sensorarray.rst:49
msgid ":tagdef:`[TechnoType]SensorArray.Warn=boolean`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/cloak/sensorarray.rst:47
msgid ""
"Whether EVA warnings and radar events should be generated if this type is"
" detected. This does not hide the unit or building from the Sensor Array,"
" and the object will still become visible. Defaults to :value:`yes`."
msgstr ""

